Drake shares CollisionGeometry instances between copies of a ProximityEngine
instance. However, CollisionObject's are unique (as they care the state
dependent poses). FCL's CollisionObject built-in constructors all perform a
write operation on the shared collision geometry -- they recompute the
geometry's local AABB. For FCL this is generally harmless; if the geometry
hasn't changed, the update produces the same values.

Drake, however, plays games with the geometry's local AABB. Based on the margin
value, we'll possibly inflate the geometry's local AABB to include the inflated
volume (note: we *don't* inflate the actual geometry). In those cases, the
margin-based AABB inflation will not survive a recomputation of the local AABB.
This, historically, has required reading the AABB, creating the collision
object, and then restoring the inflated AABB again (with an additional call to
update the object's AABB). This is not thread safe.

So, we've added a new constructor to avoid the redundant recomputation of the
local geometry's AABB. By treating the geometry truly as const during the
cloning process, one thread can read the geometry's local AABB value while
another thread is cloning safely.

We could certainly upstream this, but it probably doesn't make much sense to
do so as this only benefits off-label usage like Drake (post-hoc manipulation
of the geometry's local AABB).

--- include/fcl/narrowphase/collision_object-inl.h
+++ include/fcl/narrowphase/collision_object-inl.h
@@ -85,6 +85,23 @@ CollisionObject<S>::CollisionObject(
   computeAABB();
 }
 
+//==============================================================================
+template <typename S>
+CollisionObject<S>::CollisionObject(
+    const std::shared_ptr<CollisionGeometry<S>>& cgeom_,
+    const Transform3<S>& tf, bool local_aabb_valid)
+  : cgeom(cgeom_), cgeom_const(cgeom_), t(tf)
+{
+  if (cgeom)
+  {
+    if (!local_aabb_valid)
+    {
+      cgeom->computeLocalAABB();
+    }
+    computeAABB();
+  }
+}
+
 //==============================================================================
 template <typename S>
 CollisionObject<S>::~CollisionObject()

